91static CanvasLineCap toCanvasLineCap(LineCap lineCap)
92{
93 switch (lineCap) {
94 case ButtCap:
95 return CanvasLineCap::Butt;
96 case RoundCap:
97 return CanvasLineCap::Round;
98 case SquareCap:
99 return CanvasLineCap::Square;
100 }
101 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
102 return CanvasLineCap::Butt;
103}

106{

108 case CanvasLineCap::Butt:
109 return ButtCap;
110 case CanvasLineCap::Round:
111 return RoundCap;
112 case CanvasLineCap::Square:
113 return SquareCap;
114 }
115 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
116 return ButtCap;
117}

231void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::unwindStateStack()
232{
233 // Ensure that the state stack in the ImageBuffer's context
234 // is cleared before destruction, to avoid assertions in the
235 // GraphicsContext dtor.
236 if (size_t stackSize = m_stateStack.size()) {
237 if (auto* context = canvasBase().existingDrawingContext()) {
238 while (--stackSize)
239 context->restore();
240 }
241 }
242}
243
244CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::~CanvasRenderingContext2DBase()
245{
246#if ASSERT_ENABLED
247 unwindStateStack();
248#endif
249}

261void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::reset()
262{
263 unwindStateStack();
264 m_stateStack.resize(1);
265 m_stateStack.first() = State();
266 m_path.clear();
267 m_unrealizedSaveCount = 0;
268
269 m_recordingContext = nullptr;
270}

295String CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::State::fontString() const
296{
297 if (!font.realized())
298 return DefaultFont;
299
300 StringBuilder serializedFont;
301 const auto& font = this->font.fontDescription();
302
303 auto italic = font.italic() ? "italic " : "";
304 auto smallCaps = font.variantCaps() == FontVariantCaps::Small ? "small-caps " : "";
305 serializedFont.append(italic, smallCaps, font.computedPixelSize(), "px");
306
307 for (unsigned i = 0; i < font.familyCount(); ++i) {
308 StringView family = font.familyAt(i);
309 if (family.startsWith("-webkit-"))
310 family = family.substring(8);
311
312 auto separator = i ? ", " : " ";
313 auto quote = family.contains(' ') ? "\"" : "";
314 serializedFont.append(separator, quote, family, quote);
315 }
316
317 return serializedFont.toString();
318}

356CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::FontProxy::FontProxy(const FontProxy& other)
357 : m_font(other.m_font)
358{
359 if (realized())
360 m_font.fontSelector()->registerForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
361}
362
363auto CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::FontProxy::operator=(const FontProxy& other) -> FontProxy&
364{
365 if (realized())
366 m_font.fontSelector()->unregisterForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
367
368 m_font = other.m_font;
369
370 if (realized())
371 m_font.fontSelector()->registerForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
372
373 return *this;
374}
375
376inline void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::FontProxy::update(FontSelector& selector)
377{
378 ASSERT(&selector == m_font.fontSelector()); // This is an invariant. We should only ever be registered for callbacks on m_font.m_fonts.m_fontSelector.
379 if (realized())
380 m_font.fontSelector()->unregisterForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
381 m_font.update(&selector);
382 if (realized())
383 m_font.fontSelector()->registerForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
384 ASSERT(&selector == m_font.fontSelector());
385}
386
387void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::FontProxy::fontsNeedUpdate(FontSelector& selector)
388{
389 ASSERT_ARG(selector, &selector == m_font.fontSelector());
390 ASSERT(realized());
391
392 update(selector);
393}
394
395void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::FontProxy::initialize(FontSelector& fontSelector, const FontCascade& fontCascade)
396{
397 // Beware! m_font.fontSelector() might not point to document.fontSelector()!
398 ASSERT(fontCascade.fontSelector() == &fontSelector);
399 if (realized())
400 m_font.fontSelector()->unregisterForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
401 m_font = fontCascade;
402 m_font.update(&fontSelector);
403 ASSERT(&fontSelector == m_font.fontSelector());
404 m_font.fontSelector()->registerForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
405}

427void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::realizeSaves()
428{
429 if (m_unrealizedSaveCount)
430 realizeSavesLoop();
431
432 if (m_unrealizedSaveCount) {
433 static NeverDestroyed<String> consoleMessage(MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("CanvasRenderingContext2D.save() has been called without a matching restore() too many times. Ignoring save()."));
434
435 canvasBase().scriptExecutionContext()->addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Rendering, MessageLevel::Error, consoleMessage);
436 }
437}
438
439void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::realizeSavesLoop()
440{
441 ASSERT(m_unrealizedSaveCount);
442 ASSERT(m_stateStack.size() >= 1);
443 GraphicsContext* context = drawingContext();
444 do {
445 if (m_stateStack.size() > MaxSaveCount)
446 break;
447 m_stateStack.append(state());
448 if (context)
449 context->save();
450 } while (--m_unrealizedSaveCount);
451}
452
453void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::restore()
454{
455 if (m_unrealizedSaveCount) {
456 --m_unrealizedSaveCount;
457 return;
458 }
459 ASSERT(m_stateStack.size() >= 1);
460 if (m_stateStack.size() <= 1)
461 return;
462 m_path.transform(state().transform);
463 m_stateStack.removeLast();
464 if (std::optional<AffineTransform> inverse = state().transform.inverse())
465 m_path.transform(inverse.value());
466 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
467 if (!c)
468 return;
469 c->restore();
470}

472void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setStrokeStyle(CanvasStyle style)
473{
474 if (!style.isValid())
475 return;
476
477 if (state().strokeStyle.isEquivalentColor(style))
478 return;
479
480 if (style.isCurrentColor())
481 style = CanvasStyle(currentColor(canvasBase()).colorWithAlpha(style.overrideAlpha()));
482 else
483 checkOrigin(style.canvasPattern().get());
484
485 realizeSaves();
486 State& state = modifiableState();
487 state.strokeStyle = style;
488 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
489 if (!c)
490 return;
491 state.strokeStyle.applyStrokeColor(*c);
492 state.unparsedStrokeColor = String();
493}

647static bool lineDashSequenceIsValid(const Vector<double>& dash)
648{
649 for (size_t i = 0; i < dash.size(); i++) {
650 if (!std::isfinite(dash[i]) || dash[i] < 0)
651 return false;
652 }
653 return true;
654}
655
656void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setLineDash(const Vector<double>& dash)
657{
658 if (!lineDashSequenceIsValid(dash))
659 return;
660
661 realizeSaves();
662 modifiableState().lineDash = dash;
663 // Spec requires the concatenation of two copies the dash list when the
664 // number of elements is odd
665 if (dash.size() % 2)
666 modifiableState().lineDash.appendVector(dash);
667
668 applyLineDash();
669}
670
671void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setWebkitLineDash(const Vector<double>& dash)
672{
673 if (!lineDashSequenceIsValid(dash))
674 return;
675
676 realizeSaves();
677 modifiableState().lineDash = dash;
678
679 applyLineDash();
680}
681
682void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setLineDashOffset(double offset)
683{
684 if (!std::isfinite(offset) || state().lineDashOffset == offset)
685 return;
686
687 realizeSaves();
688 modifiableState().lineDashOffset = offset;
689 applyLineDash();
690}
691
692void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::applyLineDash() const
693{
694 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
695 if (!c)
696 return;
697 DashArray convertedLineDash(state().lineDash.size());
698 for (size_t i = 0; i < state().lineDash.size(); ++i)
699 convertedLineDash[i] = static_cast<DashArrayElement>(state().lineDash[i]);
700 c->setLineDash(convertedLineDash, state().lineDashOffset);
701}

717void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setGlobalCompositeOperation(const String& operation)
718{
719 CompositeOperator op = CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
720 BlendMode blendMode = BlendMode::Normal;
721 if (!parseCompositeAndBlendOperator(operation, op, blendMode))
722 return;
723 if ((state().globalComposite == op) && (state().globalBlend == blendMode))
724 return;
725 realizeSaves();
726 modifiableState().globalComposite = op;
727 modifiableState().globalBlend = blendMode;
728 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
729 if (!c)
730 return;
731 c->setCompositeOperation(op, blendMode);
732}
733
734void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::scale(double sx, double sy)
735{
736 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
737 if (!c)
738 return;
739 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
740 return;
741
742 if (!std::isfinite(sx) || !std::isfinite(sy))
743 return;
744
745 AffineTransform newTransform = state().transform;
746 newTransform.scaleNonUniform(sx, sy);
747 if (state().transform == newTransform)
748 return;
749
750 realizeSaves();
751
752 if (!sx || !sy) {
753 modifiableState().hasInvertibleTransform = false;
754 return;
755 }
756
757 modifiableState().transform = newTransform;
758 c->scale(FloatSize(sx, sy));
759 m_path.transform(AffineTransform().scaleNonUniform(1.0 / sx, 1.0 / sy));
760}
761
762void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::rotate(double angleInRadians)
763{
764 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
765 if (!c)
766 return;
767 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
768 return;
769
770 if (!std::isfinite(angleInRadians))
771 return;
772
773 AffineTransform newTransform = state().transform;
774 newTransform.rotate(angleInRadians / piDouble * 180.0);
775 if (state().transform == newTransform)
776 return;
777
778 realizeSaves();
779
780 modifiableState().transform = newTransform;
781 c->rotate(angleInRadians);
782 m_path.transform(AffineTransform().rotate(-angleInRadians / piDouble * 180.0));
783}
784
785void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::translate(double tx, double ty)
786{
787 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
788 if (!c)
789 return;
790 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
791 return;
792
793 if (!std::isfinite(tx) | !std::isfinite(ty))
794 return;
795
796 AffineTransform newTransform = state().transform;
797 newTransform.translate(tx, ty);
798 if (state().transform == newTransform)
799 return;
800
801 realizeSaves();
802
803 modifiableState().transform = newTransform;
804 c->translate(tx, ty);
805 m_path.transform(AffineTransform().translate(-tx, -ty));
806}
807
808void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::transform(double m11, double m12, double m21, double m22, double dx, double dy)
809{
810 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
811 if (!c)
812 return;
813 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
814 return;
815
816 if (!std::isfinite(m11) | !std::isfinite(m21) | !std::isfinite(dx) | !std::isfinite(m12) | !std::isfinite(m22) | !std::isfinite(dy))
817 return;
818
819 AffineTransform transform(m11, m12, m21, m22, dx, dy);
820 AffineTransform newTransform = state().transform * transform;
821 if (state().transform == newTransform)
822 return;
823
824 realizeSaves();
825
826 if (auto inverse = transform.inverse()) {
827 modifiableState().transform = newTransform;
828 c->concatCTM(transform);
829 m_path.transform(inverse.value());
830 return;
831 }
832 modifiableState().hasInvertibleTransform = false;
833}
834
835Ref<DOMMatrix> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::getTransform() const
836{
837 return DOMMatrix::create(state().transform.toTransformationMatrix(), DOMMatrixReadOnly::Is2D::Yes);
838}
839
840void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setTransform(double m11, double m12, double m21, double m22, double dx, double dy)
841{
842 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
843 if (!c)
844 return;
845
846 if (!std::isfinite(m11) | !std::isfinite(m21) | !std::isfinite(dx) | !std::isfinite(m12) | !std::isfinite(m22) | !std::isfinite(dy))
847 return;
848
849 resetTransform();
850 transform(m11, m12, m21, m22, dx, dy);
851}

853ExceptionOr<void> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setTransform(DOMMatrix2DInit&& matrixInit)
854{
855 auto checkValid = DOMMatrixReadOnly::validateAndFixup(matrixInit);
856 if (checkValid.hasException())
857 return checkValid.releaseException();
858
859 setTransform(matrixInit.m11.value(), matrixInit.m12.value(), matrixInit.m21.value(), matrixInit.m22.value(), matrixInit.m41.value(), matrixInit.m42.value());
860 return { };
861}

863void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::resetTransform()
864{
865 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
866 if (!c)
867 return;
868
869 AffineTransform ctm = state().transform;
870 bool hasInvertibleTransform = state().hasInvertibleTransform;
871
872 realizeSaves();
873
874 c->setCTM(canvasBase().baseTransform());
875 modifiableState().transform = AffineTransform();
876
877 if (hasInvertibleTransform)
878 m_path.transform(ctm);
879
880 modifiableState().hasInvertibleTransform = true;
881}

968static bool validateRectForCanvas(double& x, double& y, double& width, double& height)
969{
970 if (!std::isfinite(x) | !std::isfinite(y) | !std::isfinite(width) | !std::isfinite(height))
971 return false;
972
973 if (!width && !height)
974 return false;
975
976 if (width < 0) {
977 width = -width;
978 x -= width;
979 }
980
981 if (height < 0) {
982 height = -height;
983 y -= height;
984 }
985
986 return true;
987}

989static bool isFullCanvasCompositeMode(CompositeOperator op)
990{
991 // See 4.8.11.1.3 Compositing
992 // CompositeOperator::SourceAtop and CompositeOperator::DestinationOut are not listed here as the platforms already
993 // implement the specification's behavior.
994 return op == CompositeOperator::SourceIn || op == CompositeOperator::SourceOut || op == CompositeOperator::DestinationIn || op == CompositeOperator::DestinationAtop;
995}

1032void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::fillInternal(const Path& path, CanvasFillRule windingRule)
1033{
1034 auto* c = drawingContext();
1035 if (!c)
1036 return;
1037 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1038 return;
1039
1040 // If gradient size is zero, then paint nothing.
1041 auto gradient = c->fillGradient();
1042 if (gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
1043 return;
1044
1045 if (path.isEmpty())
1046 return;
1047
1048 auto savedFillRule = c->fillRule();
1049 c->setFillRule(toWindRule(windingRule));
1050
1051 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1052 if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
1053 beginCompositeLayer();
1054 c->fillPath(path);
1055 endCompositeLayer();
1056 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1057 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1058 clearCanvas();
1059 c->fillPath(path);
1060 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1061 } else
1062 c->fillPath(path);
1063
1064 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1065 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1066 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1067 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1068 else
1069 didDraw(path.fastBoundingRect());
1070
1071 c->setFillRule(savedFillRule);
1072}

1074void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::strokeInternal(const Path& path)
1075{
1076 auto* c = drawingContext();
1077 if (!c)
1078 return;
1079 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1080 return;
1081
1082 // If gradient size is zero, then paint nothing.
1083 auto gradient = c->strokeGradient();
1084 if (gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
1085 return;
1086
1087 if (path.isEmpty())
1088 return;
1089
1090 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1091 if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
1092 beginCompositeLayer();
1093 c->strokePath(path);
1094 endCompositeLayer();
1095 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1096 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1097 clearCanvas();
1098 c->strokePath(path);
1099 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1100 } else
1101 c->strokePath(path);
1102
1103 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1104 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1105 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1106 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1107 else {
1108 auto dirtyRect = path.fastBoundingRect();
1109 inflateStrokeRect(dirtyRect);
1110 didDraw(dirtyRect);
1111 }
1112}

1159
1160bool CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::isPointInPathInternal(const Path& path, double x, double y, CanvasFillRule windingRule)
1161{
1162 if (!drawingContext())
1163 return false;
1164 auto& state = this->state();
1165 if (!state.hasInvertibleTransform)
1166 return false;
1167
1168 auto transformedPoint = state.transform.inverse().value_or(AffineTransform()).mapPoint(FloatPoint(x, y));
1169 if (!std::isfinite(transformedPoint.x()) || !std::isfinite(transformedPoint.y()))
1170 return false;
1171
1172 return path.contains(transformedPoint, toWindRule(windingRule));
1173}
1174
1175bool CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::isPointInStrokeInternal(const Path& path, double x, double y)
1176{
1177 if (!drawingContext())
1178 return false;
1179 auto& state = this->state();
1180 if (!state.hasInvertibleTransform)
1181 return false;
1182
1183 auto transformedPoint = state.transform.inverse().value_or(AffineTransform()).mapPoint(FloatPoint(x, y));
1184 if (!std::isfinite(transformedPoint.x()) || !std::isfinite(transformedPoint.y()))
1185 return false;
1186
1187 return path.strokeContains(transformedPoint, [&state] (GraphicsContext& context) {
1188 context.setStrokeThickness(state.lineWidth);
1189 context.setLineCap(state.lineCap);
1190 context.setLineJoin(state.lineJoin);
1191 context.setMiterLimit(state.miterLimit);
1192 auto& lineDash = state.lineDash;
1193 DashArray convertedLineDash(lineDash.size());
1194 for (size_t i = 0; i < lineDash.size(); ++i)
1195 convertedLineDash[i] = static_cast<DashArrayElement>(lineDash[i]);
1196 context.setLineDash(convertedLineDash, state.lineDashOffset);
1197 });
1198}

1200void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::clearRect(double x, double y, double width, double height)
1201{
1202 if (!validateRectForCanvas(x, y, width, height))
1203 return;
1204 auto* context = drawingContext();
1205 if (!context)
1206 return;
1207 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1208 return;
1209 FloatRect rect(x, y, width, height);
1210
1211 bool saved = false;
1212 if (shouldDrawShadows()) {
1213 context->save();
1214 saved = true;
1215 context->setShadow(FloatSize(), 0, Color::transparentBlack, ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy);
1216 }
1217 if (state().globalAlpha != 1) {
1218 if (!saved) {
1219 context->save();
1220 saved = true;
1221 }
1222 context->setAlpha(1);
1223 }
1224 if (state().globalComposite != CompositeOperator::SourceOver) {
1225 if (!saved) {
1226 context->save();
1227 saved = true;
1228 }
1229 context->setCompositeOperation(CompositeOperator::SourceOver);
1230 }
1231 context->clearRect(rect);
1232 if (saved)
1233 context->restore();
1234 didDraw(rect);
1235}
1236
1237void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::fillRect(double x, double y, double width, double height)
1238{
1239 if (!validateRectForCanvas(x, y, width, height))
1240 return;
1241
1242 auto* c = drawingContext();
1243 if (!c)
1244 return;
1245 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1246 return;
1247
1248 // from the HTML5 Canvas spec:
1249 // If x0 = x1 and y0 = y1, then the linear gradient must paint nothing
1250 // If x0 = x1 and y0 = y1 and r0 = r1, then the radial gradient must paint nothing
1251 auto gradient = c->fillGradient();
1252 if (gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
1253 return;
1254
1255 FloatRect rect(x, y, width, height);
1256
1257 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1258 if (rectContainsCanvas(rect)) {
1259 c->fillRect(rect);
1260 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1261 } else if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
1262 beginCompositeLayer();
1263 c->fillRect(rect);
1264 endCompositeLayer();
1265 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1266 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1267 clearCanvas();
1268 c->fillRect(rect);
1269 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1270 } else
1271 c->fillRect(rect);
1272
1273 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1274 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1275 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1276 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1277 else
1278 didDraw(rect);
1279}
1280
1281void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::strokeRect(double x, double y, double width, double height)
1282{
1283 if (!validateRectForCanvas(x, y, width, height))
1284 return;
1285
1286 auto* c = drawingContext();
1287 if (!c)
1288 return;
1289 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1290 return;
1291 if (!(state().lineWidth >= 0))
1292 return;
1293
1294 // If gradient size is zero, then paint nothing.
1295 auto gradient = c->strokeGradient();
1296 if (gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
1297 return;
1298
1299 FloatRect rect(x, y, width, height);
1300 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1301 if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
1302 beginCompositeLayer();
1303 c->strokeRect(rect, state().lineWidth);
1304 endCompositeLayer();
1305 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1306 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1307 clearCanvas();
1308 c->strokeRect(rect, state().lineWidth);
1309 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1310 } else
1311 c->strokeRect(rect, state().lineWidth);
1312
1313 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1314 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1315 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1316 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1317 else {
1318 auto boundingRect = rect;
1319 boundingRect.inflate(state().lineWidth / 2);
1320 didDraw(boundingRect);
1321 }
1322}

1359void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::setShadow(const FloatSize& offset, float blur, const Color& color)
1360{
1361 if (state().shadowOffset == offset && state().shadowBlur == blur && state().shadowColor == color)
1362 return;
1363 bool wasDrawingShadows = shouldDrawShadows();
1364 realizeSaves();
1365 modifiableState().shadowOffset = offset;
1366 modifiableState().shadowBlur = blur;
1367 modifiableState().shadowColor = color;
1368 if (!wasDrawingShadows && !shouldDrawShadows())
1369 return;
1370 applyShadow();
1371}
1372
1373void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::applyShadow()
1374{
1375 auto* c = drawingContext();
1376 if (!c)
1377 return;
1378
1379 if (shouldDrawShadows()) {
1380 float width = state().shadowOffset.width();
1381 float height = state().shadowOffset.height();
1382 c->setShadow(FloatSize(width, -height), state().shadowBlur, state().shadowColor, ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy);
1383 } else
1384 c->setShadow(FloatSize(), 0, Color::transparentBlack, ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy);
1385}
1386
1387bool CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::shouldDrawShadows() const
1388{
1389 return state().shadowColor.isVisible() && (state().shadowBlur || !state().shadowOffset.isZero());
1390}

1393static LayoutSize size(HTMLImageElement& element, ImageSizeType sizeType = ImageSizeType::BeforeDevicePixelRatio)
1394{
1395 LayoutSize size;

1397 size = cachedImage->imageSizeForRenderer(element.renderer(), 1.0f); // FIXME: Not sure about this.
1398 if (sizeType == ImageSizeType::AfterDevicePixelRatio && is<RenderImage>(element.renderer()) && cachedImage->image() && !cachedImage->image()->hasRelativeWidth())
1399 size.scale(downcast<RenderImage>(*element.renderer()).imageDevicePixelRatio());
1400 }
1401 return size;
1402}

1438{

1441 LayoutSize destRectSize = size(*imageElement, ImageSizeType::AfterDevicePixelRatio);
1442 LayoutSize sourceRectSize = size(*imageElement, ImageSizeType::BeforeDevicePixelRatio);
1443 return this->drawImage(*imageElement, FloatRect { 0, 0, sourceRectSize.width(), sourceRectSize.height() }, FloatRect { dx, dy, destRectSize.width(), destRectSize.height() });
1444 },
1445 [&] (auto& element) -> ExceptionOr<void> {
1446 FloatSize elementSize = size(*element);
1447 return this->drawImage(*element, FloatRect { 0, 0, elementSize.width(), elementSize.height() }, FloatRect { dx, dy, elementSize.width(), elementSize.height() });
1448 }
1449 );

1471ExceptionOr<void> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::drawImage(HTMLImageElement& imageElement, const FloatRect& srcRect, const FloatRect& dstRect)
1472{
1473 return drawImage(imageElement, srcRect, dstRect, state().globalComposite, state().globalBlend);
1474}
1475
1476ExceptionOr<void> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::drawImage(HTMLImageElement& imageElement, const FloatRect& srcRect, const FloatRect& dstRect, const CompositeOperator& op, const BlendMode& blendMode)
1477{
1478 if (!imageElement.complete())
1479 return { };
1480 FloatRect imageRect = FloatRect(FloatPoint(), size(imageElement, ImageSizeType::BeforeDevicePixelRatio));
1481
1482 auto orientation = ImageOrientation::FromImage;
1483 if (imageElement.allowsOrientationOverride()) {
1484 if (auto* renderer = imageElement.renderer())
1485 orientation = renderer->style().imageOrientation();
1486 else if (auto* computedStyle = imageElement.computedStyle())
1487 orientation = computedStyle->imageOrientation();
1488 }
1489
1490 auto result = drawImage(imageElement.document(), imageElement.cachedImage(), imageElement.renderer(), imageRect, srcRect, dstRect, op, blendMode, orientation);
1491
1492 if (!result.hasException())
1493 checkOrigin(&imageElement);
1494 return result;
1495}

1501 if (!cachedImage || !image.document())

1504

1512
1513ExceptionOr<void> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::drawImage(Document& document, CachedImage* cachedImage, const RenderObject* renderer, const FloatRect& imageRect, const FloatRect& srcRect, const FloatRect& dstRect, const CompositeOperator& op, const BlendMode& blendMode, ImageOrientation orientation)
1514{
1515 if (!std::isfinite(dstRect.x()) || !std::isfinite(dstRect.y()) || !std::isfinite(dstRect.width()) || !std::isfinite(dstRect.height())
1516 || !std::isfinite(srcRect.x()) || !std::isfinite(srcRect.y()) || !std::isfinite(srcRect.width()) || !std::isfinite(srcRect.height()))
1517 return { };
1518
1519 if (!dstRect.width() || !dstRect.height())
1520 return { };
1521
1522 FloatRect normalizedSrcRect = normalizeRect(srcRect);
1523 FloatRect normalizedDstRect = normalizeRect(dstRect);
1524
1525 if (!srcRect.width() || !srcRect.height())
1526 return Exception { IndexSizeError };
1527
1528 // When the source rectangle is outside the source image, the source rectangle must be clipped
1529 // to the source image and the destination rectangle must be clipped in the same proportion.
1530 FloatRect originalNormalizedSrcRect = normalizedSrcRect;
1531 normalizedSrcRect.intersect(imageRect);
1532 if (normalizedSrcRect.isEmpty())
1533 return { };
1534
1535 if (normalizedSrcRect != originalNormalizedSrcRect) {
1536 normalizedDstRect.setWidth(normalizedDstRect.width() * normalizedSrcRect.width() / originalNormalizedSrcRect.width());
1537 normalizedDstRect.setHeight(normalizedDstRect.height() * normalizedSrcRect.height() / originalNormalizedSrcRect.height());
1538 if (normalizedDstRect.isEmpty())
1539 return { };
1540 }
1541
1542 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
1543 if (!c)
1544 return { };
1545 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1546 return { };
1547
1548 if (!cachedImage)
1549 return { };
1550
1551 RefPtr<Image> image = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(renderer);
1552 if (!image)
1553 return { };
1554
1555 ImageObserver* observer = image->imageObserver();
1556
1557 if (image->isSVGImage()) {
1558 image->setImageObserver(nullptr);
1559 image->setContainerSize(imageRect.size());
1560 }
1561
1562 if (image->isBitmapImage()) {
1563 // Drawing an animated image to a canvas should draw the first frame (except for a few layout tests)
1564 if (image->isAnimated() && !document.settings().animatedImageDebugCanvasDrawingEnabled())
1565 image = BitmapImage::create(image->nativeImage());
1566 downcast<BitmapImage>(*image).updateFromSettings(document.settings());
1567 }
1568
1569 ImagePaintingOptions options = { op, blendMode, orientation };
1570
1571 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1572 if (rectContainsCanvas(normalizedDstRect)) {
1573 c->drawImage(*image, normalizedDstRect, normalizedSrcRect, options);
1574 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1575 } else if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(op)) {
1576 fullCanvasCompositedDrawImage(*image, normalizedDstRect, normalizedSrcRect, op);
1577 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1578 } else if (op == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1579 clearCanvas();
1580 c->drawImage(*image, normalizedDstRect, normalizedSrcRect, options);
1581 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1582 } else
1583 c->drawImage(*image, normalizedDstRect, normalizedSrcRect, options);
1584
1585 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1586 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1587 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1588 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1589 else
1590 didDraw(normalizedDstRect);
1591
1592 if (image->isSVGImage())
1593 image->setImageObserver(observer);
1594
1595 return { };
1596}
1597
1598ExceptionOr<void> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::drawImage(CanvasBase& sourceCanvas, const FloatRect& srcRect, const FloatRect& dstRect)
1599{
1600 FloatRect srcCanvasRect = FloatRect(FloatPoint(), sourceCanvas.size());
1601
1602 if (!srcCanvasRect.width() || !srcCanvasRect.height())
1603 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
1604
1605 if (!srcRect.width() || !srcRect.height())
1606 return Exception { IndexSizeError };
1607
1608 if (!srcCanvasRect.contains(normalizeRect(srcRect)) || !dstRect.width() || !dstRect.height())
1609 return { };
1610
1611 GraphicsContext* c = drawingContext();
1612 if (!c)
1613 return { };
1614 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
1615 return { };
1616
1617 // FIXME: Do this through platform-independent GraphicsContext API.
1618 ImageBuffer* buffer = sourceCanvas.buffer();
1619 if (!buffer)
1620 return { };
1621
1622 checkOrigin(&sourceCanvas);
1623
1624 sourceCanvas.makeRenderingResultsAvailable();
1625
1626 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
1627 if (rectContainsCanvas(dstRect)) {
1628 c->drawImageBuffer(*buffer, dstRect, srcRect, { state().globalComposite, state().globalBlend });
1629 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1630 } else if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
1631 fullCanvasCompositedDrawImage(*buffer, dstRect, srcRect, state().globalComposite);
1632 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1633 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
1634 if (&sourceCanvas == &canvasBase()) {
1635 if (auto copy = buffer->copyRectToBuffer(srcRect, colorSpace(), *c)) {
1636 clearCanvas();
1637 c->drawImageBuffer(*copy, dstRect, { { }, srcRect.size() }, { state().globalComposite, state().globalBlend });
1638 }
1639 } else {
1640 clearCanvas();
1641 c->drawImageBuffer(*buffer, dstRect, srcRect, { state().globalComposite, state().globalBlend });
1642 }
1643 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
1644 } else
1645 c->drawImageBuffer(*buffer, dstRect, srcRect, { state().globalComposite, state().globalBlend });
1646
1647 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
1648 didDraw(std::nullopt);
1649 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
1650 didDrawEntireCanvas();
1651 else
1652 didDraw(dstRect);
1653
1654 return { };
1655}

1806template<class T> IntRect CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::calculateCompositingBufferRect(const T& area, IntSize* croppedOffset)
1807{
1808 IntRect canvasRect(0, 0, canvasBase().width(), canvasBase().height());
1809 canvasRect = canvasBase().baseTransform().mapRect(canvasRect);
1810 Path path = transformAreaToDevice(area);
1811 IntRect bufferRect = enclosingIntRect(path.fastBoundingRect());
1812 IntPoint originalLocation = bufferRect.location();
1813 bufferRect.intersect(canvasRect);
1814 if (croppedOffset)
1815 *croppedOffset = originalLocation - bufferRect.location();
1816 return bufferRect;
1817}

1819RefPtr<ImageBuffer> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::createCompositingBuffer(const IntRect& bufferRect)
1820{
1821 return ImageBuffer::create(bufferRect.size(), isAccelerated() ? RenderingMode::Accelerated : RenderingMode::Unaccelerated, 1, colorSpace(), pixelFormat());
1822}
1823
1824void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::compositeBuffer(ImageBuffer& buffer, const IntRect& bufferRect, CompositeOperator op)
1825{
1826 IntRect canvasRect(0, 0, canvasBase().width(), canvasBase().height());
1827 canvasRect = canvasBase().baseTransform().mapRect(canvasRect);
1828
1829 auto* c = drawingContext();
1830 if (!c)
1831 return;
1832
1833 c->save();
1834 c->setCTM(AffineTransform());
1835 c->setCompositeOperation(op);
1836
1837 c->save();
1838 c->clipOut(bufferRect);
1839 c->clearRect(canvasRect);
1840 c->restore();
1841 c->drawImageBuffer(buffer, bufferRect.location(), state().globalComposite);
1842 c->restore();
1843}

1854
1855template<class T> void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::fullCanvasCompositedDrawImage(T& image, const FloatRect& dest, const FloatRect& src, CompositeOperator op)
1856{
1857 ASSERT(isFullCanvasCompositeMode(op));
1858
1859 IntSize croppedOffset;
1860 auto bufferRect = calculateCompositingBufferRect(dest, &croppedOffset);
1861 if (bufferRect.isEmpty()) {
1862 clearCanvas();
1863 return;
1864 }
1865
1866 auto buffer = createCompositingBuffer(bufferRect);
1867 if (!buffer)
1868 return;
1869
1870 auto* c = drawingContext();
1871 if (!c)
1872 return;
1873
1874 FloatRect adjustedDest = dest;
1875 adjustedDest.setLocation(FloatPoint(0, 0));
1876 AffineTransform effectiveTransform = c->getCTM();
1877 IntRect transformedAdjustedRect = enclosingIntRect(effectiveTransform.mapRect(adjustedDest));
1878 buffer->context().translate(-transformedAdjustedRect.location());
1879 buffer->context().translate(croppedOffset);
1880 buffer->context().concatCTM(effectiveTransform);
1881 drawImageToContext(image, buffer->context(), adjustedDest, src, { CompositeOperator::SourceOver });
1882
1883 compositeBuffer(*buffer, bufferRect, op);
1884}

1960
1961ExceptionOr<RefPtr<CanvasPattern>> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::createPattern(HTMLImageElement& imageElement, bool repeatX, bool repeatY)
1962{
1963 auto* cachedImage = imageElement.cachedImage();
1964
1965 // If the image loading hasn't started or the image is not complete, it is not fully decodable.
1966 if (!cachedImage || !imageElement.complete())
1967 return nullptr;
1968
1969 if (cachedImage->status() == CachedResource::LoadError)
1970 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
1971
1972 bool originClean = cachedImage->isOriginClean(canvasBase().securityOrigin());
1973
1974 // FIXME: SVG images with animations can switch between clean and dirty (leaking cross-origin
1975 // data). We should either:
1976 // 1) Take a fixed snapshot of an SVG image when creating a pattern and determine then whether
1977 // the origin is clean.
1978 // 2) Dynamically verify the origin checks at draw time, and dirty the canvas accordingly.
1979 // To be on the safe side, taint the origin for all patterns containing SVG images for now.
1980 if (cachedImage->image()->isSVGImage())
1981 originClean = false;
1982
1983 auto* image = cachedImage->imageForRenderer(imageElement.renderer());
1984 if (!image)
1985 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
1986
1987 auto nativeImage = image->nativeImage();
1988 if (!nativeImage)
1989 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
1990
1991 return RefPtr<CanvasPattern> { CanvasPattern::create(nativeImage.releaseNonNull(), repeatX, repeatY, originClean) };
1992}
1993
1994ExceptionOr<RefPtr<CanvasPattern>> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::createPattern(CanvasBase& canvas, bool repeatX, bool repeatY)
1995{
1996 if (!canvas.width() || !canvas.height())
1997 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
1998 auto* copiedImage = canvas.copiedImage();
1999
2000 if (!copiedImage)
2001 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
2002
2003 auto nativeImage = copiedImage->nativeImage();
2004 if (!nativeImage)
2005 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
2006
2007 return RefPtr<CanvasPattern> { CanvasPattern::create(nativeImage.releaseNonNull(), repeatX, repeatY, canvas.originClean()) };
2008}

2051void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::didDrawEntireCanvas()
2052{
2053 didDraw(backingStoreBounds(), DidDrawOption::ApplyClip);
2054}
2055
2056void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::didDraw(std::optional<FloatRect> rect, OptionSet<DidDrawOption> options)
2057{
2058 if (!drawingContext())
2059 return;
2060
2061 if (!rect) {
2062 canvasBase().didDraw(std::nullopt);
2063 return;
2064 }
2065
2066 auto dirtyRect = rect.value();
2067 if (dirtyRect.isEmpty())
2068 return;
2069
2070 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
2071 return;
2072
2073 if (options.contains(DidDrawOption::ApplyTransform))
2074 dirtyRect = state().transform.mapRect(dirtyRect);
2075
2076 if (options.contains(DidDrawOption::ApplyShadow) && state().shadowColor.isVisible()) {
2077 // The shadow gets applied after transformation
2078 auto shadowRect = dirtyRect;
2079 shadowRect.move(state().shadowOffset);
2080 shadowRect.inflate(state().shadowBlur);
2081 dirtyRect.unite(shadowRect);
2082 }
2083
2084 // FIXME: This does not apply the clip because we have no way of reading the clip out of the GraphicsContext.
2085
2086 if (m_dirtyRect.contains(dirtyRect))
2087 canvasBase().didDraw(std::nullopt);
2088 else {
2089 m_dirtyRect.unite(dirtyRect);
2090 canvasBase().didDraw(m_dirtyRect);
2091 }
2092}

2095{
2096 m_dirtyRect = { };
2097}

2110void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::paintRenderingResultsToCanvas()
2111{
2112 if (!m_recordingContext)
2113 return;
2114
2115 ASSERT(m_usesDisplayListDrawing);
2116
2117 auto& displayList = m_recordingContext->displayList();
2118 if (!displayList.isEmpty()) {
2119 DisplayList::Replayer replayer(*canvasBase().drawingContext(), displayList);
2120 replayer.replay(backingStoreBounds());
2121 displayList.clear();
2122 }
2123}

2142bool CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::needsPreparationForDisplay() const

2175ExceptionOr<Ref<ImageData>> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::getImageData(int sx, int sy, int sw, int sh, std::optional<ImageDataSettings> settings) const
2176{

2226{
2227 ImageBuffer* buffer = canvasBase().buffer();
2228 if (!buffer)
2229 return;
2230
2231 if (data.data().isDetached())
2232 return;
2233
2234 if (dirtyWidth < 0) {
2235 dirtyX += dirtyWidth;
2236 dirtyWidth = -dirtyWidth;
2237 }
2238
2239 if (dirtyHeight < 0) {
2240 dirtyY += dirtyHeight;
2241 dirtyHeight = -dirtyHeight;
2242 }
2243
2244 IntRect clipRect { dirtyX, dirtyY, dirtyWidth, dirtyHeight };
2245 clipRect.intersect(IntRect { 0, 0, data.width(), data.height() });
2246 IntSize destOffset { dx, dy };
2247 IntRect destRect = clipRect;
2248 destRect.move(destOffset);
2249 destRect.intersect(IntRect { { }, buffer->logicalSize() });
2250 if (destRect.isEmpty())
2251 return;
2252 IntRect sourceRect { destRect };
2253 sourceRect.move(-destOffset);
2254 sourceRect.intersect(IntRect { 0, 0, data.width(), data.height() });
2255
2256 if (!sourceRect.isEmpty())
2257 buffer->putPixelBuffer(data.pixelBuffer(), sourceRect, IntPoint { destOffset });
2258
2259 didDraw(FloatRect { destRect }, { }); // ignore transform, shadow and clip

2262void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::inflateStrokeRect(FloatRect& rect) const
2263{
2264 // Fast approximation of the stroke's bounding rect.
2265 // This yields a slightly oversized rect but is very fast
2266 // compared to Path::strokeBoundingRect().
2267 static const float root2 = sqrtf(2);
2268 float delta = state().lineWidth / 2;
2269 if (state().lineJoin == MiterJoin)
2270 delta *= state().miterLimit;
2271 else if (state().lineCap == SquareCap)
2272 delta *= root2;
2273 rect.inflate(delta);
2274}

2355bool CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::canDrawText(double x, double y, bool fill, std::optional<double> maxWidth)
2356{
2357 if (!fontProxy()->realized())
2358 return false;
2359
2360 auto* c = drawingContext();
2361 if (!c)
2362 return false;
2363 if (!state().hasInvertibleTransform)
2364 return false;
2365 if (!std::isfinite(x) | !std::isfinite(y))
2366 return false;
2367 if (maxWidth && (!std::isfinite(maxWidth.value()) || maxWidth.value() <= 0))
2368 return false;
2369
2370 // If gradient size is zero, nothing would be painted.
2371 auto gradient = c->strokeGradient();
2372 if (!fill && gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
2373 return false;
2374
2375 gradient = c->fillGradient();
2376 if (fill && gradient && gradient->isZeroSize())
2377 return false;
2378
2379 return true;
2380}
2381
2382static inline bool isSpaceThatNeedsReplacing(UChar c)
2383{
2384 // According to specification all space characters should be replaced with 0x0020 space character.
2385 // http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/the-canvas-element.html#text-preparation-algorithm
2386 // The space characters according to specification are : U+0020, U+0009, U+000A, U+000C, and U+000D.
2387 // http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/common-microsyntaxes.html#space-character
2388 // This function returns true for 0x000B also, so that this is backward compatible.
2389 // Otherwise, the test LayoutTests/canvas/philip/tests/2d.text.draw.space.collapse.space.html will fail
2390 return c == 0x0009 || c == 0x000A || c == 0x000B || c == 0x000C || c == 0x000D;
2391}
2392
2393String CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::normalizeSpaces(const String& text)
2394{
2395 size_t i = text.find(isSpaceThatNeedsReplacing);
2396 if (i == notFound)
2397 return text;
2398
2399 unsigned textLength = text.length();
2400 Vector<UChar> charVector(textLength);
2401 StringView(text).getCharactersWithUpconvert(charVector.data());
2402
2403 charVector[i++] = ' ';
2404
2405 for (; i < textLength; ++i) {
2406 if (isSpaceThatNeedsReplacing(charVector[i]))
2407 charVector[i] = ' ';
2408 }
2409 return String::adopt(WTFMove(charVector));
2410}

2423void CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::drawTextUnchecked(const TextRun& textRun, double x, double y, bool fill, std::optional<double> maxWidth)
2424{
2425 auto* c = drawingContext();
2426 auto& fontProxy = *this->fontProxy();
2427 const auto& fontMetrics = fontProxy.fontMetrics();
2428
2429 // FIXME: Need to turn off font smoothing.
2430
2431 float fontWidth = fontProxy.width(textRun);
2432 bool useMaxWidth = maxWidth && maxWidth.value() < fontWidth;
2433 float width = useMaxWidth ? maxWidth.value() : fontWidth;
2434 FloatPoint location(x, y);
2435 location += textOffset(width, textRun.direction());
2436
2437 // The slop built in to this mask rect matches the heuristic used in FontCGWin.cpp for GDI text.
2438 FloatRect textRect = FloatRect(location.x() - fontMetrics.height() / 2, location.y() - fontMetrics.ascent() - fontMetrics.lineGap(),
2439 width + fontMetrics.height(), fontMetrics.lineSpacing());
2440 if (!fill)
2441 inflateStrokeRect(textRect);
2442
2443#if USE(CG)
2444 const CanvasStyle& drawStyle = fill ? state().fillStyle : state().strokeStyle;
2445 if (drawStyle.canvasGradient() || drawStyle.canvasPattern()) {
2446 IntRect maskRect = enclosingIntRect(textRect);
2447
2448 // If we have a shadow, we need to draw it before the mask operation.
2449 // Follow a procedure similar to paintTextWithShadows in TextPainter.
2450
2451 if (shouldDrawShadows()) {
2452 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(*c);
2453
2454 FloatSize offset(0, 2 * maskRect.height());
2455
2456 FloatSize shadowOffset;
2457 float shadowRadius;
2458 Color shadowColor;
2459 c->getShadow(shadowOffset, shadowRadius, shadowColor);
2460
2461 FloatRect shadowRect(maskRect);
2462 shadowRect.inflate(shadowRadius * 1.4);
2463 shadowRect.move(shadowOffset * -1);
2464 c->clip(shadowRect);
2465
2466 shadowOffset += offset;
2467
2468 c->setShadow(shadowOffset, shadowRadius, shadowColor, ShadowRadiusMode::Legacy);
2469
2470 if (fill)
2471 c->setFillColor(Color::black);
2472 else
2473 c->setStrokeColor(Color::black);
2474
2475 fontProxy.drawBidiText(*c, textRun, location + offset, FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2476 }
2477
2478 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(*c);
2479
2480 auto paintMaskImage = [&] (GraphicsContext& maskImageContext) {
2481 if (fill)
2482 maskImageContext.setFillColor(Color::black);
2483 else {
2484 maskImageContext.setStrokeColor(Color::black);
2485 maskImageContext.setStrokeThickness(c->strokeThickness());
2486 }
2487
2488 maskImageContext.setTextDrawingMode(fill ? TextDrawingMode::Fill : TextDrawingMode::Stroke);
2489
2490 if (useMaxWidth) {
2491 maskImageContext.translate(location - maskRect.location());
2492 // We draw when fontWidth is 0 so compositing operations (eg, a "copy" op) still work.
2493 maskImageContext.scale(FloatSize((fontWidth > 0 ? (width / fontWidth) : 0), 1));
2494 fontProxy.drawBidiText(maskImageContext, textRun, FloatPoint(0, 0), FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2495 } else {
2496 maskImageContext.translate(-maskRect.location());
2497 fontProxy.drawBidiText(maskImageContext, textRun, location, FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2498 }
2499 };
2500
2501 // FIXME: Handling gradients and patterns by painting the text into a mask is probably the wrong thing to do in the presence of color glyphs.
2502 if (c->clipToDrawingCommands(maskRect, colorSpace(), WTFMove(paintMaskImage)) == GraphicsContext::ClipToDrawingCommandsResult::FailedToCreateImageBuffer)
2503 return;
2504
2505 drawStyle.applyFillColor(*c);
2506 c->fillRect(maskRect);
2507 return;
2508 }
2509#endif
2510
2511 c->setTextDrawingMode(fill ? TextDrawingMode::Fill : TextDrawingMode::Stroke);
2512
2513 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(*c);
2514 if (useMaxWidth) {
2515 c->translate(location);
2516 // We draw when fontWidth is 0 so compositing operations (eg, a "copy" op) still work.
2517 c->scale(FloatSize((fontWidth > 0 ? (width / fontWidth) : 0), 1));
2518 location = FloatPoint();
2519 }
2520
2521 bool repaintEntireCanvas = false;
2522 if (isFullCanvasCompositeMode(state().globalComposite)) {
2523 beginCompositeLayer();
2524 fontProxy.drawBidiText(*c, textRun, location, FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2525 endCompositeLayer();
2526 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
2527 } else if (state().globalComposite == CompositeOperator::Copy) {
2528 clearCanvas();
2529 fontProxy.drawBidiText(*c, textRun, location, FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2530 repaintEntireCanvas = true;
2531 } else
2532 fontProxy.drawBidiText(*c, textRun, location, FontCascade::UseFallbackIfFontNotReady);
2533
2534 if (isEntireBackingStoreDirty())
2535 didDraw(std::nullopt);
2536 else if (repaintEntireCanvas)
2537 didDrawEntireCanvas();
2538 else
2539 didDraw(textRect);
2540}

2550Ref<TextMetrics> CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::measureTextInternal(const TextRun& textRun)
2551{
2552 Ref<TextMetrics> metrics = TextMetrics::create();
2553
2554 auto& font = *fontProxy();
2555 auto& fontMetrics = font.fontMetrics();
2556
2557 GlyphOverflow glyphOverflow;
2558 glyphOverflow.computeBounds = true;
2559 float fontWidth = font.width(textRun, &glyphOverflow);
2560 metrics->setWidth(fontWidth);
2561
2562 FloatPoint offset = textOffset(fontWidth, textRun.direction());
2563
2564 metrics->setActualBoundingBoxAscent(glyphOverflow.top - offset.y());
2565 metrics->setActualBoundingBoxDescent(glyphOverflow.bottom + offset.y());
2566 metrics->setFontBoundingBoxAscent(fontMetrics.ascent() - offset.y());
2567 metrics->setFontBoundingBoxDescent(fontMetrics.descent() + offset.y());
2568 metrics->setEmHeightAscent(fontMetrics.ascent() - offset.y());
2569 metrics->setEmHeightDescent(fontMetrics.descent() + offset.y());
2570 metrics->setHangingBaseline(fontMetrics.ascent() - offset.y());
2571 metrics->setAlphabeticBaseline(-offset.y());
2572 metrics->setIdeographicBaseline(-fontMetrics.descent() - offset.y());
2573
2574 metrics->setActualBoundingBoxLeft(glyphOverflow.left - offset.x());
2575 metrics->setActualBoundingBoxRight(fontWidth + glyphOverflow.right + offset.x());
2576
2577 return metrics;
2578}
2579
2580FloatPoint CanvasRenderingContext2DBase::textOffset(float width, TextDirection direction)
2581{
2582 auto& fontMetrics = fontProxy()->fontMetrics();
2583 FloatPoint offset;
2584
2585 switch (state().textBaseline) {
2586 case TopTextBaseline:
2587 case HangingTextBaseline:
2588 offset.setY(fontMetrics.ascent());
2589 break;
2590 case BottomTextBaseline:
2591 case IdeographicTextBaseline:
2592 offset.setY(-fontMetrics.descent());
2593 break;
2594 case MiddleTextBaseline:
2595 offset.setY(fontMetrics.height() / 2 - fontMetrics.descent());
2596 break;
2597 case AlphabeticTextBaseline:
2598 default:
2599 break;
2600 }
2601
2602 bool isRTL = direction == TextDirection::RTL;
2603 auto align = state().textAlign;
2604 if (align == StartTextAlign)
2605 align = isRTL ? RightTextAlign : LeftTextAlign;
2606 else if (align == EndTextAlign)
2607 align = isRTL ? LeftTextAlign : RightTextAlign;
2608
2609 switch (align) {
2610 case CenterTextAlign:
2611 offset.setX(-width / 2);
2612 break;
2613 case RightTextAlign:
2614 offset.setX(-width);
2615 break;
2616 default:
2617 break;
2618 }
2619 return offset;
2620}
